    <header>
        <img src="logo.png" alt="ICUC Logo">
        <h1>Islamic Call University College (ICUC)</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <h2>15–Point Website Audit Guide</h2>
        <p style="max-width:700px;">
            This guide helps Web Design & Development students at ICUC evaluate websites 
            professionally using a clear scoring system. Each point below carries 2 marks for a total of 30 marks.
        </p>

        <div class="audit-list">

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>1. Header & Branding</h3>
                <p>Check whether the website has a clear identity — logo, site title, tagline, and consistent university branding.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>2. Navigation Clarity</h3>
                <p>Menus should be simple, easy to find, and provide logical paths for users.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>3. Visual Design & Aesthetic</h3>
                <p>Evaluate overall beauty of the site — spacing, alignment, colors, and graphical balance.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>4. Typography & Readability</h3>
                <p>Text should be readable, well-sized, and consistent across pages.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>5. Colour Harmony</h3>
                <p>Colours must blend well, match the brand, and not strain the eyes. ICUC green (#0b6623) should stand out.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>6. Responsiveness (Mobile/Tablet)</h3>
                <p>Check whether the design adapts to different screens without breaking layout.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>7. Page Layout Structure</h3>
                <p>A good layout should have clear sections, balanced spacing, and a logical flow.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>8. Content Depth</h3>
                <p>Pages should contain meaningful information, not shallow text or filler content.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>9. Content Accuracy & Clarity</h3>
                <p>Ensure correct grammar, correct information, and clear explanations tailored to the audience.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>10. Multimedia Use (Images, Videos)</h3>
                <p>Are multimedia elements relevant, high quality, optimized, and used professionally?</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>11. Functionality & Interactivity</h3>
                <p>Check buttons, links, forms, animations, and any interactive elements for proper functionality.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>12. Loading Speed</h3>
                <p>Fast-loading websites improve user experience. Evaluate image sizes, scripts, and optimization.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>13. Professionalism & Trustworthiness</h3>
                <p>The website should reflect a credible institution through tone, accuracy, and presentation.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>14. Consistency Across Pages</h3>
                <p>Check whether all pages maintain the same colors, fonts, button styles, and structure.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="audit-item">
                <h3>15. Overall User Experience (UX)</h3>
                <p>Evaluate how enjoyable and easy the site is to use. UX should consider emotions and convenience.</p>
            </div>

        </div>

        <a href="index.html" class="back-btn">Back to Group Page</a>
    </div>

